cliff shunned meeting us at meals ; yet he
would not consent, formally, to exclude Hare-
ton and Cathy. He had an aversion to yield-
ing so completely to his feelings, chosing, ra-
ther, to absent himself'—And eating once in
twenty-four hours seemed suﬂicient sustenance
for him.

